OL,7,FThe Police Misconduct Panel was right
OL,8,Fnot to dismiss an officer in Greater
OL,9,FManchester who had sex with a
OL,10,Fcolleague on police premises while on
OL,11,Fduty, a High Court judge has ruled.
OL,13,FInspector Alex Taylor was given a
OL,14,Ffinal written warning to sit on his
OL,15,Frecord for four years, after it
OL,16,Femerged that he began a relationship
OL,17,Fwith a police community support
OL,18,Fofficer (PCSO) in early 2020 by
OL,19,Fexchanging "flirty and then overtly
OL,20,Fsexual" messages on WhatsApp.
