OL,5,Cjudge rules
OL,7,F"A reasonable member of the public
OL,8,Fwould be aware of all the
OL,9,Fcircumstances of the relationship
OL,10,Fbetween Inspector Taylor and the PCSO:
OL,11,Fthat it was a consensual relationship;
OL,12,Fthat it had not rested on any misuse
OL,13,Fof a position of authority; that
OL,14,FInspector Taylor's decision-making had
OL,15,Fbeen impaired by depression; that the
OL,16,Frelationship had been short-lived; and
OL,17,Fthat it had not had any significant
OL,18,Fimpact on policing.
